{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n`rebar review-code` (the local/coding-agent path) reviews a diff but persists NOTHING — only the\nGerrit voter emits a `code_review` artifact. Without a local artifact there is no per-session memory\nfor the region-gated novelty floor (blameless-grindable-noctule) to converge against. This story\nmakes local `review-code` emit a session-keyed `code_review` artifact, reusing the payload/reader\nshape from revenued-thickset-dassie.\n\n## What\n- **Resolve the local memory key.** Use the centralized\n  `rebar._commands.session_id.resolve_session_id()` (precedence: `REBAR_SESSION_ID` →\n  `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` → `OPENCODE_SESSION_ID` → `SESSION_ID`; validated shared-across-subagents,\n  unique-per-parallel-session).\n  - **Fallback (approach A):** when it returns `None` (bare/headless, no SessionStart shim), mint a\n    per-invocation `uuid4` (do NOT persist a shared file). This guarantees ISOLATION — no\n    local→Gerrit bleed and no cross-session contamination — at the cost of making local convergence\n    intentionally INERT for a bare invocation (each run gets a fresh key, so the reader finds no\n    prior). Genuine per-session convergence arrives wherever a session lifecycle exists (native\n    harness var or a SessionStart shim exporting `REBAR_SESSION_ID`).\n- **Set `session_id` on the verdict.** The local path sets `verdict[\"session_id\"] = session_key` so\n  the payload (revenued-thickset-dassie's `build_payload`, which reads `verdict.get(\"session_id\")`)\n  carries it top-level. The typed memory key for the reader is `session:<session_key>`.\n- **Wire the local gate entry to emit + persist.** Thread the resolved key down the local call chain\n  `_review_code → shim.review_code → gate_dispatch.produce_code_review_verdict` and emit a session-keyed\n  artifact:\n  - **Signature changes (in scope):** add `target_ticket: str | None = None` and\n    `session_id: str | None = None` parameters to `code_review/shim.py::review_code(...)`, AND add a\n    `session_id: str | None = None` field to the `CodeReviewRequest` dataclass in `gate_dispatch.py`\n    (alongside the existing `target_ticket`). The shim forwards both onto\n    `CodeReviewRequest(target_ticket=…, session_id=…, …)`. Without these the resolved key cannot\n    reach the emit path.\n  - **Create-or-reuse idempotency (session key = stable convergence point).** Before emitting, a\n    local-emit helper resolves ONE artifact ticket per session key, mirroring\n    `voter.emit_code_review_artifact` (voter.py ~199–220) EXACTLY:\n    `title = f\"code-review: session:{session_key}\"`; scan\n    `rebar.list_tickets(ticket_type=\"code_review\", repo_root=repo_root)` for a title match and REUSE\n    that artifact id; else `rebar.create_ticket(\"code_review\", title, …)`. Then `sidecar.emit(verdict,\n    target_ticket=artifact_id, …)`. So two sequential local reviews under one session id append\n    sidecar events to the SAME artifact (AC4) instead of duplicating.\n  - **`relates_to` link (best-effort).** Link the artifact `relates_to` the resolved work ticket\n    (from `--ticket` or the head commit's `rebar-ticket:` trailer) for searchability. A\n    trailerless/ticketless review STILL persists (memory is keyed by session, not by ticket) — the\n    only degradation is no cross-run match when the key differs; a missing link never fails the review.\n  - **Best-effort throughout:** artifact create/reuse/emit/link failures are logged and swallowed —\n    they must NEVER fail the review (mirrors the voter + sidecar posture).\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py` (`_review_code`: resolve key, thread it down),\n  `src/rebar/llm/code_review/shim.py` (`review_code`: add `target_ticket`/`session_id` params),\n  `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py` (local-emit helper: create-or-reuse the session artifact\n  + set `verdict[\"session_id\"]`).\n- Depends on the payload shape + reader (revenued-thickset-dassie).\n- OUT of scope: the Gerrit voter path (already emits; inherits the payload extension); the\n  region_gated_floor consumer (blameless-grindable-noctule).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Local `rebar review-code` emits a `code_review` artifact keyed `session:<id>` carrying the\n      reviewed-file `deps` map and a top-level `session_id`.\n- [ ] The session key = `resolve_session_id()`; when `None`, a per-invocation `uuid4` is used (no\n      shared-file persistence), making bare-invocation local convergence intentionally inert.\n- [ ] `shim.review_code` gains `target_ticket` + `session_id` parameters and `CodeReviewRequest`\n      gains a `session_id` field, both forwarded, so the local path can supply the artifact anchor\n      and session key.\n- [ ] Create-or-reuse idempotency: two sequential local reviews under ONE session id append to the\n      SAME artifact (title `code-review: session:{id}`), not duplicate tickets.\n- [ ] The artifact `relates_to`-links the resolved ticket when one is available; a trailerless/\n      ticketless review still persists (keyed by session) and never fails the review.\n- [ ] Tests: a local review with a set `REBAR_SESSION_ID` emits/reuses one session-keyed artifact\n      across two runs; a bare review (no session var) mints a uuid key and still persists; artifact\n      failures never fail the review."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783647878207552001,"uuid":"754772b6-142a-4e2f-a6bb-a8b5022c036c"}